## Errors & Mistakes
The original version of this commit bundled an apt robustness workaround with the SM103 change. That apt workaround was based on a real prior arm64 CI failure on main where the inherited ubuntu-toolchain-r Launchpad PPA could not be reached, and on a pattern from origin/alex-ddtree-vllm-image. However, it broadened the PR beyond the user's desired SM103 change. The user explicitly objected to the apt-management changes, so they were removed. This may cause the refreshed PR CI to hit the same arm64 apt/PPA failure that the earlier broader commit avoided.

## Dead Ends
No new alternate implementation was pursued after the user clarified the scope. A separate fixup commit was avoided because it would leave the PR history showing the unwanted apt changes and then their removal. Amending keeps the draft PR's branch diff focused.

## Hints for Future Agents
If the refreshed GitHub Actions run fails on arm64 during apt-get update/install against ppa.launchpadcontent.net or ubuntu-toolchain-r, that failure is likely unrelated to SM103 compilation. Do not silently reintroduce the PPA removal or apt retry workaround unless the user agrees to that broader change. The desired SM103 behavior is still to transform the base arch list so 10.3a is present and to filter only plain sm_103/compute_103 in NVCC_WRAPPER_FILTER_CODES. Do not filter sm_103a or compute_103a, because those are the outputs this change is trying to preserve.

